    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-01T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-01T05:00:00-05:00" n="498"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363/11–144: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-01T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >November 1, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 1—11:08 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4190. I have sent a note to Molotov<note n="78" xml:id="d498fn78">Vyacheslav
                        Mikhailovich Molotov, People’s Commissar for Foreign Affairs of the Soviet
                        Union.</note> this afternoon following closely the line of the Department’s
                    2566, October 30, 10 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
